I"H<p>In his short story title “Closer”, Greg Egan explores how two individuals can perfectly share their <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brain-waves-are-consonant-with-momentariness">momentary experiences</a>. Their <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/manifolds-formalize-emergence">neural manifolds</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/spatial-metaphors-provide-primitives-for-latent-space-navigation">are modified to meet half-way through</a> in the latent space of latent spaces (i.e. the meta manifold of different possible neural manifolds).</p>
